<h1>Setting Up Your Application</h1>

<p>
  Você pode iniciar um projeto Winnetou do zero ou adicionar os constructos e funcionalidades da library em seu código existente. Aqui mostraremos como iniciar um app do inicio.
</p>

<h2>
  Tudo o que você precisa, em 3 linhas.
</h2>

<p>
  Para iniciar um projeto Winnetou do zero, abra o terminal e digite:
</p>


<pre class="terminal">
  npm init -y;
  npm install --save-dev winnetoujs;
  node scaffolding;
</pre>

<p>
  <code>npm init -y;</code> Para iniciar um projeto que pode instalar módulos da npm.
</p>

<p>
  <code>npm install --save-dev winnetoujs;</code> Instala o framework em seu projeto.
</p>

<p>
  <code>node scaffolding;</code> (Opicional) Copia os arquivos de um projeto inicial para o seu diretório.
</p>

<h2>Configuration File</h2>
<p>
  Well, before we see how to start a WinnetouJs project and write our first Constructo, it is necessary to understand the configuration of the project and also the file structure.

  The configuration file is called win.config.js and it is there that we define all the locations of the project files.
</p>

<div class="codeOutput">
  <span class="code-file-name">win.config.js</span>
  <pre><code class="onloadCode">
      
export default {
    constructosPath: "./constructos",
    constructosOut: "./js/constructos",
    entry: "./js/app.js",
    out: "./release",
    folderName: "/",
    sass: "./sass",
    cssOut:"./release/css",
    css: "./css",
    icons: "./icons",
    coloredIcons: "./coloredIcons",
    defaultLang: "en-us",
};
     
    </code></pre>
</div>

<p>
  It must be at the same level as wbr.js and node_modules.
</p>

<h2>Visual Studio Code and JSDoc</h2>
<p>
  WinnetouJs is passionate about VanillaJs and we believe in the potential and freedom of javascript. That's why we don't use any abstraction in our native code, like typescript for example. However, we believe in clean, maintainable and reusable code, so all classes generated by WBR have been fed by descriptions using <b>jsdoc</b>. As we recommend Visual Studio Code as an editor for Winnetou, we advise you to download/enable the extension that supports jsdoc within VSCode for a better development experience.</p>





